1772067776853467	bones-dev	itc:v3:AWKSZJkkk5JkmZMxAAAAQatWqrq1bWwAAAE3AQ		item.create	bn-3ap	{"description":"The generator (generate → candidate → hash) can produce 4+ char hashes with no digits (e.g. 'ncvq'). parse_id rejects these because of the intentional rule: hashes with 4+ chars must contain at least one digit (to avoid ambiguity with English words). This means generate() can return IDs that parse_id() considers invalid — a soundness bug. Discovered via bones: bn create generated bn-ncvq, but 'bn triage dep add bn-ncvq --blocks bn-2po3' rejected it as 'invalid item ID format: bn-ncvq'. Fix: the generator should retry or inject a digit when the candidate hash is 4+ chars and all-letters, ensuring every generated ID round-trips through parse_id.","kind":"task","title":"Generator produces IDs that fail parse_id validation"}	blake3:-YURWnm3LEJUaoiYWEHPRJy5sX2vT203Qk5FQ4cQkYA
